    .example(style='border:none')
      table.chi-table.-bordered.-mt--3.-mb--3
        thead
          tr
            th Level
            th Change
        tbody
          tr
            td Atom
            td
              b a
              | -classname__extension
              i.-ml--1.chi-icon.-xs.icon-chevron-right.-icon--muted
              code.-ml--1 chi-classname__extension
          tr
            td Molecule
            td
              b m
              | -classname__extension
              i.-ml--1.chi-icon.-xs.icon-chevron-right.-icon--muted
              code.-ml--1 chi-classname__extension
          tr
            td Organism
            td
              b o
              | -classname__extension
              i.-ml--1.chi-icon.-xs.icon-chevron-right.-icon--muted
              code.-ml--1 chi-classname__extension
          tr
            td Template
            td
              b t
              | -classname__extension
              i.-ml--1.chi-icon.-xs.icon-chevron-right.-icon--muted
              code.-ml--1 chi-classname__extension
          tr
            td Page
            td
              b p
              | -classname__extension
              i.-ml--1.chi-icon.-xs.icon-chevron-right.-icon--muted
              code.-ml--1 chi-classname__extension
    p.-text
      | In order to use Chi 2.0 it is necessary to update classnames that are currently in use in your project.
    ul#chi-2-tabs-classname-replacement.chi-tabs.-border.-sm
      li.-active
        a(href='#replacement-unix') For Unix users
      li
        a(href='#replacement-windows') For Windows users
    #replacement-unix.chi-tabs-panel.-active
      .-pt--1
        p.-text
          | 1. Download the <code>replace.sh</code> script from Chi's repository:
        :code(lang='html')
          https://github.com/CenturyLinkCloud/ux-chi/tree/master/scripts/chi-classnames/bash
        p.-text
          | 2. Place the Bash script in a folder together with your project to achieve this file structure:
        :code(lang='html')
          /replacement_folder
              |── /project_folder
              |── replace.sh
        p.-text
          | 3. Open <code>replace.sh</code> with IDE and change variable <code>PROJECT_SRC</code> with the path corresponding to your project folder:
        :code(lang='html')
          PROJECT_SRC='project_folder'
        p.-text
          | 4. Open terminal, go to the directory with <code>replace.sh</code> and assign necessary permissions to it:
        :code(lang='html')
          $ chmod +x replace.sh
        p.-text
          | 5. Launch <code>replace.sh</code> script:
        :code(lang='html')
          $ ./replace.sh
        p.-text
          | 6. Verify Atomic prefixes are correctly replaced.

    #replacement-windows.chi-tabs-panel
